cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to disambiguate biomedical named entities. The use of deep learning models such as convolutional neural networks and long short-term memory networks suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the task of disambiguating named entities involves information retrieval and classification, which could place the paper under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of deep learning models for classification suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
